==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#The [[headgear]] with which a horse is governed and which carries a [[bit]] and [[reins]].
#A [[length]] of [[line]] or [[cable]] attached to [[two]] parts of something to [[spread]] the [[force]] of a [[pull]], as the rigging on a [[kite]] for attaching [[line]].

====Etymology====
Old English ''[[brīdel]]''

====Translations====
{{top}}
*French: [[bride]]
{{mid}}
*[[Ido]]: [[brido]]
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|bridl|ing}}

#{{transitive}} To put a bridle on.
#{{transitive}} To [[check]], [[restrain]], or [[control]] with, or as if with, a bridle; as , ''bridle your [[tongue]]''.
#{{intransitive}} To [[show]] [[hostility]] or [[resentment]].

